[[File:MC 09-0173-005 - Flickr - NZ Defence Force.jpg|thumb|The New Zealand Defence Force Marine Engineering Synthetic Training Environment is used to train Navy ship crews in an interactive full simulation setting.]]
[[File:Ship Handling Simulator at Maritime Warfare Centre (Visakhapatnam).jpg|thumb|Ship Handling Simulator at Maritime Warfare Centre, [[Visakhapatnam]]]]
{{Redirect|Ship simulator|the video game|Ship Simulator (video game)}}

A '''maritime simulator''' or '''ship simulator''' is a system that [[simulation|simulates]] [[ship]]s and maritime environments for training, research and other purposes. Today, simulator training given by maritime schools and academies is part of the basic training of maritime professionals.

At minimum, a maritime simulator consists of a software that realistically simulates the dynamic behavior of a vessel and its systems in a simulated maritime environment and an interface that allows the person using the simulator to control the vessel and interact with its simulated surroundings. In case of so-called full mission bridge simulators, this interface consists of a realistic mock-up of the vessel's [[Bridge (nautical)|bridge]] and control consoles, and screens or projectors providing up to 360-degree virtual view of the ship's surroundings similar to [[flight simulator]]s in the aviation industry. Without the real-time visualization, the simulation software can also be used for "fast time" simulations where the vessels are controlled by autopilot.<ref>[http://www.marin.nl/web/Facilities-Tools/Simulators/Simulator-Facilities/Fasttime-Simulators.htm Fast-time Simulators]. Marin. {{retrieved|accessdate=2016-11-12}}</ref> In addition, there are maritime simulators for e.g. [[ECDIS]],<ref>[http://imagesoft.fi/fi/product/is-ecdis-simulator/ IS ECDIS Simulator]. Image Soft. {{retrieved|accessdate=2016-11-12}}</ref> [[engine room]],<ref>[http://www.transas.com/products/simulation/engine-room-and-cargo-handling-simulators/ERS5000 ERS 5000 Engine Room Simulator]. Transas. {{retrieved|accessdate=2016-11-12}}</ref> and cargo handling operations,<ref>[http://www.transas.com/products/simulation/engine-room-and-cargo-handling-simulators/LCHS5000 Transas Liquid Cargo Handling Simulator]. Transas. {{retrieved|accessdate=2016-11-12}}</ref> as well as shore-side operations such as [[vessel traffic service|Vessel Traffic Service (VTS)]].<ref>[http://www.aboamare.fi/VTS-Simulator VTS Simulator]. Aboa Mare. {{retrieved|accessdate=2016-11-12}}</ref>

Maritime simulator games such as [[Ship Simulator (video game)|''Ship Simulator'']] and ''[[Virtual Sailor]]'' are also available for home users.

