{{other uses|Storming Heaven (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Storming Heaven | orig title = | translator = | image = Storming Heaven (Giardina novel).jpg <!--prefer 1st edition--> | caption = | author = [[Denise Giardina]] | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | genre = [[Historical novel]] | publisher = | release_date = [[1987 in literature|1987]] | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover|Hardback]] and [[Paperback]]) | pages = | isbn = 0-393-02440-7 | dewey= 813/.54 19 | congress= PS3557.I136 S76 1987 | oclc= 14413378 | preceded_by = [[Good King Harry (novel)|Good King Harry]] | followed_by = [[The Unquiet Earth]] }}
'''''Storming Heaven''''' is [[Denise Giardina]]'s second novel. It was published in 1987 and won the [[W.D. Weatherford Award]] that year.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.berea.edu/appalachiancenter/weatherford/pastwinners.asp | title = Weatherford Award | accessdate = August 12, 2007 }}</ref> It is a fictionalized account of the labor strife in the coalfields of southern [[West Virginia]], United States during 1920 and 1921.
