{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox journal | title = The British Art Journal | cover = | editor = [[Robin Simon (critic)|Robin Simon]] | discipline = [[Art history]]; [[British art]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Br. Art J. | publisher = Art Journals Ltd | country = UK | frequency = 3 times a year | history = 1999–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.britishartjournal.co.uk/ | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = britartj | OCLC = 43427170 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 1467-2006 | eISSN = }}
'''''The British Art Journal''''' is a [[Wiktionary:triannual|triannual]] journal/magazine that publishes research on [[British art]] from all historical periods.
==History== The publication was launched on 1 July 1999 at a reception held at the [[Thomas Coram Foundation]] (which became the [[Foundling Museum]]) in [[London]]. Two issues were published in the initial year. Since then, three issues have been published each year.<ref name="worldcate">{{cite web| url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/british-art-journal/oclc/43427170 | title=The British art journal | publisher=[[WorldCat]] | accessdate=29 May 2018 }}</ref>
The editor is the British [[art historian]] and [[Art critic|critic]], [[Robin Simon (critic)|Robin Simon]]. The journal is accessible online through [[JSTOR]].<ref name="jstor">{{cite web| url=https://www.jstor.org/journal/britartj | title=The British Art Journal | publisher=[[JSTOR]] | accessdate=29 May 2018 }}</ref>
